Unfortunately, everyone uses statically-typed languages wrong, so they get about the same protection with their compiler that you get with Ruby or Perl or Python.<p>Consider this common mistake:<p><pre><code>   interface Greet {
       void sayHello(String firstName, String lastName)
   }

   class PrintGreeter implements Greet {
       public void sayHello(String lastName, String firstName) {
           ...
       }
   }
</code></pre>
Where&#x27;s your compiler NOW?
